<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post120725"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>essig</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Cleric</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Aug 2002<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 30</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">We need a way to make mobs die faster. Either increase our damage output, or give us a way to increase the damage output of the group, or a debuff that makes mobs easier to kill. There needs to be a reason to bring a cleric along when you don't need tons of healing (i.e. outside of a raid). Ok, I know these aren't specific ideas, but I think any upgrades we get should be along these lines.<br />
<br />
Things I don't want to see as part of the priest balancing:<br />
<br />
* Improved ability to kill undead. This might be fun and nice, but there just isn't enough undead for this to be worth it. I'd rather not 'waste' any upgrades we may get on undead killing power.<br />
* Solo abilities. If they increase our damage output, our solo abilities may go up some. That is fine. But I always felt that a cleric was a defensive player who increased the power of a group. I like this role and would rather see that role enhanced rather than being able to solo well.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	<p align="right"><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><a href="report.php?s=c1f700b24b72665146d2f5737ab3b58d&postid=120725">Report this post to a moderator</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=c1f700b24b72665146d2f5737ab3b58d&action=getip&postid=120725">Logged</a></font></p>
