	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">1. Change Summoned Hammer to Self only Imbue Weapon, and scale it back down the levels.<br />
<br />
2. Increase Def and maybe Dodge.<br />
<br />
3. Change the Hammer Pet into a real Pet. Low HP/AC due to the fact that we can buff. In the end it gets all the melee goodness other pets get, therefore negating our need for increased melee skills and thus keeping up from becoming something we are not (melee) and stepping on peoples toes. Also scale back pet to lvl 34/39. This alone would solve our Solo issues and allow us to bring more DPS to an XP grind. We could sit and med and heal... all the while out Pet is dishing the goods... heck we could even duo with our pet and our Imbued weapon!<br />
<br />
4. Give us an Avatar form similar to the Animal forms Druids and Shamans get. Gives mana regen, levitate, and some focus affect (open to suggestions here).<br />
<br />
5. Fix the yaulp line, Pally's shouldn't get V and VI. Whatever it was on test before the change would be nice (ie not the Str, lower AC, neg Sta that it is now).<br />
<br />
Thats all i got, i think we should focus on making the Cleric inherrently more desireable... not making zones that make Clerics more desirable. We are the masters of Healing... but just like wizards have THE best DD spells in the game, there are other classes that can cast DD spells... and now just like them we share the spotlight with Druids and Shamans, no biggie here. Undead spells? I rarely get the chance to use them, and i hate swithcing between Live and Undead dmg spells... more Undead zones is just a waste of time, and more undead mobs in the game will just irritate me as i'll have to switch spells (a minor inconvienence i know, but look at everyone screaming about PoTG?).<br />
