<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post120758"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Norab</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Cleric</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Oct 1999<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 53</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b>buff / increase party damage output</b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Fundamentally, the first poster is right.  We need a way to vastly increase the damage output of a party, or we will always be back in the same boat.<br />
<br />
Some ideas:<br />
1) Make cleric yaulp castable on others<br />
2) Make a significant improvement to mark of retribution (scale it with damage shield of other classes), whats 15/hit when the shaman has it 70% slowed or another class has a 1600 point DOT on it?<br />
3) Allow us to buff 'attack' (IE yaulp above)<br />
4) Give us 'buffs' that increase spell damage, and melee damage significantly (these must be short duration buffs of course, so people actually want us in the group, not just buffs as we run by)<br />
5) Make mark of karn functional in the real world high end game, its quite an original spell idea, but its completely overshadowed by the damage a high end greature does.  In order to get us desired by groups, it needs to at least be restored to its original form (10 points of healing per hit), and even that at 60+ may be too little.<br />
6) Give us mana free damage ability, like other classes have, such as items that allow us to 'click' cast nukes, etc. <br />
7) If our pet is going to continue to go away after one combat session, then the damage output must be VASTLY, VASTLY higher.  It needs to be wicked, and feared if its all we are going to be able to do to increase damage output.<br />
<br />
Its important to note, that in an experience group, its USUALLY all about MANA FREE damage output.. Epic dots, or pets, or click nukes/dots, or the ability to get mana back faster than you spend it.      <br />
<br />
Norab</font></p>
	
