	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I would like to see our pet removed from game. It does not suit our class nor is it what you would envision a cleric having for a companion.<br />
<br />
I would however like to see a constant companion in our travels much the same as a wizards familiar. With other clericish abilities that can include any combination of the following:<br />
<br />
-Cast Divine Aura on his owner once per game day.<br />
-Give the owner constant ultravsion.<br />
-Act as a holy or unholy 2 or 3 point damage shield, diety depending, on the owner.<br />
-The ability to cast Divine Light on his owner once per game day.<br />
-It would act as a greater light source.<br />
-Imbue any weapon with hand of the gods.<br />
-Add 5% spell haste to your group.<br />
-Add 5% mele (spell) haste to your group.<br />
-Increase our specialization checks.<br />
-Decrease owners fizzle rate.<br />
-Add a small amount of mana regen to his owner (I actually don't like this idea but others do).<br />
<br />
The guardian can be any of a bunch of graphics a hammer, an imp, tiny water pet (epic thing) or anything you can think of really.<br />
<br />
Another alter idea would be to have a few very specific guardians you could call depending on your group type. IE<br />
<br />
Mele group:<br />
Haste + dmg shield<br />
<br />
Caster group<br />
Mana pres + mana regen<br />
<br />
Solo<br />
Hammer proc + Fizzle rate lowering + spec checks<br />
<br />
All of the additions are small because they are meant to add to a groups casters abilities not replace them. The guardian can take the place of a blessing line of spells and in fact can be the guardian angel or devil of the group.<br />
<br />
Will think more on this. Please PM any ideas you have to add to or take from this. Ill be happy to change it around.</font></p>
	
