	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post120807"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Gello</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Exarch</font><br>
	<img src="avatar.php?userid=1871&dateline=1037045543" border="0" alt=""><p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Apr 2000<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 932</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>It's very important that clerics have an ability that makes other players say "I really want to invite a cleric because they can do X, and that will be really helpful."<hr></blockquote>If the intent is to get clerics into pickup groups easier without increasing their already overpowerful raiding utility, this would work:<br />
<br />
Blessing of the Reverence - +10% spell haste (+15% to mage ring) <br />
Blessing of the Brimstone - +1-10% improved damage (+1-20% to mage bracer) <br />
Blessing of the Prudent - +1-5% mana preservation (+1-10% to MP3/4) <br />
Blessing of the Devout - +1-10% improved healing (+1-20% IH3/4) <br />
Blessing of the Meek - +10% extend affliction (+20% EA3/4)<br />
Blessing of the Pious - +10% extend enchantment (+20% EE3/4)<br />
<br />
Mages and raid-class gear will surpass these for raiding types so it won't be cast at raids.  This line of spells would most benefit the clerics LFG (pickup groups probably won't have a ton of focus IV gear), the ones most impacted by druids and shamans taking cleric spots in groups.  It wouldn't step on mage toes too much since mages can provide better.  It would make having a cleric in the group a 'blessing' but not a necessity.<br />
<br />
I personally don't think any more really needs to be done with the class, but my own perception may be a bit out of touch.  1) I know I'd be a poor game designer, 2) I never fail to have a few people looking for stuff for me to do seconds after I log in, 3) I can contribute meaningful damage to a group and I can actually kill blue stuff solo if I want.<br />
<br />
edit: no snare or invis.  It doesn't fit the cleric as a class.  Necs sulk around and fear kite, hitting a fleeing mob until it dies.  It's not very "lawful" (if you consider clerics should be lawful good/neutral/evil by ADnD standards) and doesn't fit the cleric pathos.  No diety wants their disciples hidden or killing the defenseless.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6938" target="_blank">Gello</a>, Iksar Cleric in the Lost Asylum</font></p></p>
