	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I think the Mark Line (although situational) could have many uses.<br />
Some have Suggested Mark of Mana.  Or a mark where damage is increased each time the mob is hit.  Or even a mark where the mob's AC is dropped. But how about:<br />
<br />
Mark of Haterd : Increased whomever is attacking the on the mob's hate list even more.<br />
<br />
Mark of Interruption: Each time the mob is hit there is a chance that the mob is hit with a interruption (0.0 stun).<br />
<br />
Mark of Silence: There is an increased chance that the mob's spell will be interrupted.<br />
<br />
Mark of a Feeble Mind: Increase the casting time of mobs (like starting at 10 percent)<br />
<br />
This would mean that Complete heal for affected mobs will be 11 secs.  Not earth shattering but who know what can happen in that extra second.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	<p align="right"><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><a href="report.php?s=c1f700b24b72665146d2f5737ab3b58d&postid=120816">Report this post to a moderator</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=c1f700b24b72665146d2f5737ab3b58d&action=getip&postid=120816">Logged</a></font></p>
